BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Toronto Social Events
X-SOURCE-URL:https://www.meetup.com/toronto/
UID:event_313991277@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260404T025345Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260404T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260404T150000
SUMMARY:English Spanish Language Conversation
DESCRIPTION:Language Exchange Toronto - Se Habla English & Spanish\n**Span
 ish Language Conversation Toronto** is part of ***Se Habla.***\n\n**“Se 
 Habla”** is a leading online community for cultural and linguistic excha
 nge where you can participate in enriching sessions\, make new friends\, a
 nd connect with a growing global network. With 9 Meetup groups across 9 ci
 ties in 6 countries\, Se Habla is truly open to everyone from Alaska to Pa
 tagonia\, and from Europe and Asia to Australia. Join us and don’t miss 
 the opportunity to practice with native speakers.\n\n**We have been meetin
 g since June 2020 on the following days:**\n\n* Monday\n* Wednesday\n* Fri
 day\n* Saturday\n* Sunday\n\nWith a one-time donation\, you can join the m
 eetings as many times as you like and stay as long as you wish.\n\n**Forma
 t**\n**Conversation Rooms (Everyday and All levels)**\nDepending on attend
 ance and nationality\, small groups are formed with 4-6 people:\n\n* 2 nat
 ive English speakers\n* 2 native Spanish speakers\n* 1 native speaker of a
 nother language\n\nThe meetings last for 2 hours and are divided into 4 pe
 riods:\n\n* 30 minutes speaking in English\n* 30 minutes speaking in Spani
 sh\n* 30 minutes speaking in English\n* 30 minutes speaking in Spanish\n\n
 **Beginner Room (Optional and only Mondays)**\nWelcome\, English and Spani
 sh beginners.\n**Check the English and Spanish lessons** here **»** [http
 s://myspanishclass.xyz/](https://myspanishclass.xyz/)\n\n**Debate Room (Op
 tional and only Wednesday)**\nNew topic each week.\n**Check the discussion
  topics here »** [https://se-habla.com/category/article/](https://se-habl
 a.com/category/article/)\n\nPlease note that **we speak half of the time i
 n English and half in Spanish.** We help each other learn both languages.\
 n\n**After two hours**\, everyone returns to the main room to meet all par
 ticipants and take a group screenshot. If you have time\, you’re welcome
  to stay and continue the conversation for as long as you like.\n\n**Commu
 nity**\n**We have 9 MeetUp groups meeting at the same time** (Mexico City\
 , Calgary\, Vancouver\, Toronto\, New York\, London\, Los Angeles\, Medell
 ín\, and Santiago de Chile). However\, during the exchange\, you will mee
 t people not only from these cities but also from all over the world.\n\nY
 ou can get the link to our 9 MeetUp groups by visiting any of the followin
 g pages:\n[https://se-habla.com/spanish-meetup/](https://se-habla.com/span
 ish-meetup/)\n[[https://se-habla.com/english-meetup/](https://se-habla.com
 /english-meetup/)\n\n**One-Time Donation**\nFor over four years\, the meet
 ings were free\, but currently I am requesting a **ONE-TIME DONATION** to 
 access the meetings and help to cover the costs of the 9 MeetUp Groups and
  Zoom.\n\nYou can make the one-time donation at the link below. Afterward\
 , PayPal will redirect you to a page where you'll find the Zoom link to jo
 in the meeting.\n[https://se-habla.com/language-exchange](https://se-habla
 .com/language-exchange/)\n\nIf you have already donated and don't have the
  Zoom link\, please contact me.\n\n**Please don’t hesitate to reach out 
 if you have any further questions.**\n\nSee you soon\,\n**Héctor Fuentes*
 *
